Products.Name: Ocean Chef Hoki Fillets
Products.SupplyLimitMessage: 'Ocean Chef Hoki Fillets' has a supply limit of 36. The quantity in your cart has been reduced accordingly. To purchase a larger quantity, please contact us on 1800 000 610. Please note we do not supply trade orders.
Products.RichDescription:
Our wild caught Blue Grenadier, also known as Hoki are caught in the deep, open waters of New Zealand. With a delicate flavour and moist, flakey flesh, these versatile fillets can be fried, grilled, baked or barbecued.
Try a tempura batter or light crumb and serve up with chips and a salad for a delicious home-style take-away.
STORAGE INSTRUCTIONS:
Store below minus 18°C. Once thawed, keep refrigerated below 4°C and consume within 48 hours. Do not refreeze.

THAWING:
To thaw place desired quantity of hoki fillets in refrigerator at below 4°C for approximately 8 hours.

While efforts have been made to remove bones, the occasional bone may remain.

This seafood has met the MSC's global standards for sutainability. www.msc.org
